	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Some gameplay ideas. 
<br />
<br />1) Have a visible "world" you are protecting at bottom of the screen which gets damaged for every missile that gets past you
<br />2) Have the "world" do something each new round based on how well the world is doing. If the world isn't damaged it should give you some maximum benefit (as to what I'm not sure), if it's damaged greatly the "world" helps you less.
<br />3) Make the enemy missiles shootable so you can block them killing the world.
<br />
<br />With these ideas it adds a little bit of persistence to the world round to round . Maybe some kind of optional "choose a building to build" type thing at the end of each round where the building does something unique, giving players a choice.
<br />
<br />These ideas might already be in some space invaders games, after playing thousands of games it's hard to know what is original or not in your own head.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


